MacroHedgeExecutorForkTest::deployableMint
├── when resolveAndMint is called with the demo long call params and a positive size
│   ├── it should mint the demo position through the executor
│   ├── it should leave numberOfLegs of the executor greater than zero
│   └── it should emit PositionMinted and RepresentativenessAssessed with requestId zero on the direct path
├── when quoteCollateralRequirements is read after the funded mint
│   └── it should return a BalanceDelta without reverting
├── when a second executor is funded with nonzero collateral far below the position requirement and called with the identical params
│   ├── it should revert AccountInsolvent on the resolveAndMint call
│   └── it should leave numberOfLegs of the underfunded executor at zero after the revert
└── when resolveAndMint is called with legParams size exceeding one hundred twenty seven
    └── it should revert on the shared sink optionRatio overflow guard
